MAMELODI Sundowns goalkeeper Ricardo Goss has shared his message for supporters over the Easter weekend. Goss has called for caution over the Easter weekend as people travel across the country. He has also emphasized the importance of obeying the Covid-19 regulations. “I would like wish everyone a happy Easter weekend,” said Goss. “But I would like to urge everyone to continue wearing their masks and sanitizing regularly to protect yourselves against Covid-19. “I would also like to urge people to not drink and drive as they go to their different destinations.” Sundowns are currently in Sudan where they face Al Hilal in their Caf Champions League encounter at Al Hilal Stadium in Khartoum on Friday (3pm).